parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rearview camera can increase the risk of accidents or injuries while reversing, as the driver may not be able to see obstacles or people behind the vehicle.
symptoms: The rearview camera displays a blank or blue screen
the image is distorted or upside down
the camera is unavailable or not operable
the message "Camera Unavailable" is displayed on the infotainment screen
the camera image is cloudy or pixilated
the camera is flashing on and off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Corrosion and fracture of the battery can cause the vehicle to stall, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls
warning lights illuminate
the battery is corroded
fractured
and leaking
the starter fails to function.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the backup camera can decrease driver visibility, increasing the risk of accidents or injuries when reversing.
symptoms: The camera displays an upside-down image
the image fails to appear
the parking guide lines fail to display
the camera remains on while driving forward
the image flashes off to black.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system issues can cause unexpected behavior, such as the radio turning on when the car is off, which can be a distraction and increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The radio turns on when the car is off
the radio turns off while driving
the radio comes on full volume while parked and unattended.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden and unexplained shattering of the sunroof can cause glass fragments to fall inside the vehicle, posing a risk to occupants' safety and potentially causing injuries.
symptoms: The sunroof shatters without any apparent impact or debris
often accompanied by a loud noise
and leaves a hole and cracked glass.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction or failure of the backup camera can increase the risk of accidents or injuries, particularly when reversing, as it is a critical safety component.
symptoms: The backup camera works intermittently or fails to function altogether
often requiring replacement.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unidentified clunking or popping noise under the front end of the vehicle can be unsettling and potentially indicate a more serious underlying issue, affecting the vehicle's safety and performance.
symptoms: A loud
clunking or popping noise occurs under the front end of the vehicle
often when turning or backing into a parking space
without any apparent correlation to temperature or road conditions.
